== libn ==

*libn* is a lightweight and less sucky alternative to Glib and GObject or
Boost. libn lets you write elegant C code in an object-oriented manner with
the help of mruby.


== About libn ==

libn is written and maintained by Christian Koch <cfkoch@sdf.lonestar.org>.

The source code is released under a 2-clause BSD-style license. See the
LICENSE file for details.
